---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const featured=(await getCollection('articles',({data})=>data.status==='published'&&data.featured)).slice(0,3);
---
<Base transparentHeader title="Dunhuang Within — Enter Dunhuang. Listen Inward." description="A modern inner journey through Dunhuang: paths, practices, symbols, stories, and objects of intention for the space between chapters.">
<section class="hero hero-dunhuang"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">A Place Between Worlds</p><p class="hero-brand">Dunhuang Within</p><h1>Enter Dunhuang. Listen inward.</h1><p class="lede">Follow a modern inner journey through desert, cave, manuscript, and mural—for the moments when the old path no longer fits.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/find-your-path/">Find Your Path</a><a class="button secondary" href="/places/dunhuang/">Enter Dunhuang</a><a class="button shop-highlight" href="/objects/">Shop Objects of Intention</a></div></div></section>

<section class="daily-trace"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">Today’s trace</p><p>What was hidden was not lost. Some things wait until we are ready to read them.</p><a href="/places/dunhuang/cave-17/">Enter Cave 17 →</a></div></section>

<section class="section dark path-entry"><div class="wrap builder-feature"><div><p class="eyebrow">The first step is personal</p><h2>What are you moving through?</h2><p class="lede">Noise. Uncertainty. A chapter ending. A search for meaning. Begin there, and receive a Dunhuang-inspired path with a practical way to enter it.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/find-your-path/">Find My Dunhuang Path</a></div></div><div class="builder-preview" aria-label="Example path result"><div class="preview-row"><span>Current state</span><strong>Between chapters</strong></div><div class="preview-row"><span>Seeking</span><strong>Clarity</strong></div><div class="preview-row"><span>Landscape</span><strong>Desert</strong></div><div class="preview-row"><span>Your path</span><strong>The Desert Crossing</strong></div></div></div></section>

<section class="dunhuang dunhuang-origin"><div class="wrap origin-grid"><div><p class="eyebrow">40.14° N, 94.66° E</p><h2>Dunhuang</h2></div><div><h3>A place that learned to hold many worlds.</h3><p class="lede">Desert and oasis. Routes and caves. Manuscripts in many languages. A thousand years of attention gathered at the edge of uncertainty.</p><p>Dunhuang Within begins with documented history, then clearly names the modern reflection we draw from it.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/brand-story/">Our Story</a><a class="button secondary" href="/dunhuang-map/">Explore the Trail Map</a></div></div></div></section>

<section class="story-chapters"><article><div class="chapter-copy"><p class="eyebrow">I · Origin</p><h2>What the desert preserved.</h2><p>Dunhuang’s power begins in a real place: an oasis sustaining passage, caves shaped by devotion, and images made to carry meaning across generations.</p><a href="/places/dunhuang/">Enter the historical world →</a></div><div class="story-image origin-image" aria-hidden="true"></div></article><article><div class="chapter-copy"><p class="eyebrow">II · Passage</p><h2>What you practice today.</h2><p>A path becomes real through repetition: ten minutes of silence, a walk without input, a question written by hand, a day protected from noise.</p><a href="/practices/">Explore practices →</a></div><div class="story-image passage-image" aria-hidden="true"></div></article><article><div class="chapter-copy"><p class="eyebrow">III · Return</p><h2>What you carry back.</h2><p>The journey returns to ordinary life. A word, a symbol, or one small object may hold an intention close—but it does not promise, protect, or cure on its own.</p><a href="/objects/">Discover objects of intention →</a></div><div class="story-image return-image" aria-hidden="true"></div></article></section>

<section class="section paths-section"><div class="wrap"><div class="intro-grid"><p class="eyebrow">Paths</p><div><h2>One place. Different ways through.</h2><p class="section-copy">Each path joins a Dunhuang landscape with a modern transition. They are editorial frameworks, not ancient doctrines.</p></div></div><div class="path-list"><a href="/paths/#desert-crossing"><span>01</span><strong>The Desert Crossing</strong><em>Courage for uncertainty</em></a><a href="/paths/#hidden-cave"><span>02</span><strong>The Hidden Cave</strong><em>Listening inward</em></a><a href="/paths/#oasis-return"><span>03</span><strong>The Oasis Return</strong><em>Enoughness and renewal</em></a><a href="/paths/#silk-road"><span>04</span><strong>The Silk Road Path</strong><em>Direction without certainty</em></a></div></div></section>

<section class="section material-memory"><div class="wrap"><div class="intro-grid"><p class="eyebrow">Material Memory</p><div><h2>Before an object, there is a material story.</h2><p class="section-copy">Future Dunhuang Within objects will begin with traceable materials, responsible cultural context, and a clear intention—not unsupported energy claims.</p></div></div><div class="material-grid"><a href="/symbols/#cave"><span>Stone</span><strong>Shelter · endurance · carved attention</strong></a><a href="/places/dunhuang/manuscripts/"><span>Paper</span><strong>Memory · language · what survives</strong></a><a href="/places/dunhuang/murals/"><span>Mineral color</span><strong>Image · devotion · time</strong></a><a href="/objects/"><span>Metal & cord</span><strong>Weight · touch · daily return</strong></a></div></div></section>

<section class="section dark carry-section"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">Carry the Path</p><h2>An object does not contain the journey. It helps you remember it.</h2><p class="lede">Future pendants, bracelets, journals, and symbolic objects will connect a documented Dunhuang source with a path and a simple daily practice. No fake relics. No guaranteed fortune. No medical claims.</p><div class="carry-flow"><span>Historical source</span><span>Symbol</span><span>Practice</span><span>Object</span><span>Daily return</span></div><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/objects/">See the Object Principles</a></div></div></section>

<section class="section keepers"><div class="wrap"><div class="intro-grid"><p class="eyebrow">The work behind the wonder</p><div><h2>Meaning survives because people keep it.</h2><p class="section-copy">Conservators protect fragile caves. Scholars reconnect dispersed manuscripts. Digital teams expand access. Artists and educators help new audiences look with context.</p></div></div><div class="needs-list"><a class="need-row" href="/places/dunhuang/mogao-caves/"><strong>Conservation</strong><span>Protecting a vulnerable cave environment</span><span>→</span></a><a class="need-row" href="/places/dunhuang/international-dunhuang-programme/"><strong>Reconnection</strong><span>Bringing dispersed archives into shared study</span><span>→</span></a><a class="need-row" href="/places/dunhuang/murals/"><strong>Interpretation</strong><span>Seeing images through history before symbolism</span><span>→</span></a></div></div></section>

<section class="map-invitation"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">Travel · Buddha Traces · Myth & Murals</p><h2>Follow Dunhuang across three maps.</h2><p>Move between physical places, Buddhist art, and painted stories. Select a point to reveal the landscape behind it.</p><a class="button" href="/dunhuang-map/">Open the Trail Map</a></div></section>

<section class="section tint"><div class="wrap"><p class="eyebrow">Journal</p><h2>Stories for a longer relationship.</h2><div class="editorial-grid">{featured.map((article,index)=><a class:list={["story",{lead:index===0}]} href={`/${article.id}/`}><span class="story-meta">{article.data.cluster.replaceAll('-',' ')} · {index===0?'7':'5'} min</span><h3>{article.data.title}</h3><p>{article.data.description}</p></a>)}</div><div class="actions"><a class="button secondary" href="/journal/">Open the Journal</a></div></div></section>
<section class="section home-objects-stories"><div class="wrap"><div class="intro-grid"><p class="eyebrow">Objects & Offerings</p><div><h2>Every object begins with a story.</h2><p class="section-copy">A future bracelet, pendant, journal or tactile ritual object should carry more than a motif. It should begin with the cultural world that made the image meaningful.</p></div></div><div class="home-objects-grid"><a href="/places/dunhuang/nine-colored-deer-meaning/"><span>Mural story</span><strong>The Nine-Colored Deer</strong><p>Compassion, trust, and discernment in a painted narrative.</p></a><a href="/places/dunhuang/three-hares-meaning/"><span>Symbol story</span><strong>The Three Hares</strong><p>A small circular motif that holds relationship and movement.</p></a><a href="/places/dunhuang/dunhuang-colors-meaning/"><span>Material story</span><strong>Mineral Color</strong><p>How a palette can remember place without imitating a relic.</p></a></div><div class="actions"><a class="button home-objects-button" href="/journal/">Read Objects & Offerings</a><a class="button secondary" href="/objects/">Explore the Shop</a></div></div></section>
<section class="section"><div class="wrap"><Newsletter /></div></section>
</Base>
<style is:global>
.hero-dunhuang:before{background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(14,15,12,.96),rgba(14,15,12,.58) 52%,rgba(14,15,12,.2)),linear-gradient(0deg,var(--ink-deep),transparent 36%),url('/images/dunhuang/worlds-mural.jpg') center/cover!important;filter:saturate(.72)}.daily-trace{padding:1.4rem 0;background:var(--sand-light)}.daily-trace .wrap{display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr auto;gap:2rem;align-items:center}.daily-trace .eyebrow{margin:0;color:var(--ink-deep)}.daily-trace p:not(.eyebrow){margin:0;font:italic 1.18rem var(--serif)}.daily-trace a{text-decoration:none;font-size:.72rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em}.path-entry{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--ink-deep),rgba(23,24,19,.88) 56%,rgba(23,24,19,.38)),url('/images/dunhuang/cave-buddha.jpg') right center/55% auto no-repeat}.dunhuang-origin{min-height:82vh;align-items:center;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--ink-deep),rgba(23,24,19,.88) 48%,rgba(23,24,19,.25)),linear-gradient(0deg,var(--ink-deep),transparent 30%,transparent 70%,var(--ink-deep)),url('/images/dunhuang/desert-oasis.jpg') 78% center/cover!important}.origin-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.1fr .9fr;gap:8vw;align-items:end}.story-chapters{background:var(--ink-soft);color:var(--moonlight)}.story-chapters article{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.2fr;min-height:72vh}.story-chapters article:nth-child(even){grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr}.story-chapters article:nth-child(even) .chapter-copy{order:2}.chapter-copy{display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;padding:8vw}.chapter-copy p{max-width:560px}.story-image{min-height:420px}.origin-image{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--ink-soft),transparent 30%),url('/images/dunhuang/reclining-buddha.jpg') center/cover}.passage-image{background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent 70%,var(--ink-soft)),url('/images/dunhuang/desert-caravan.jpg') center/cover}.return-image{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--ink-soft),transparent 30%),url('/images/dunhuang/nine-colored-deer.jpg') center/cover}.path-list{margin-top:4rem;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}.path-list a{display:grid;grid-template-columns:4rem 1fr auto;gap:1rem;align-items:center;padding:1.6rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);text-decoration:none}.path-list strong{font:400 clamp(1.7rem,4vw,3.7rem) var(--serif)}.path-list em{font-style:normal;color:var(--oxidized-jade)}.material-memory{background:var(--sand-pale)}.material-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);margin-top:4rem;border-block:1px solid var(--line)}.material-grid a{display:flex;min-height:260px;flex-direction:column;justify-content:space-between;padding:1.5rem;border-right:1px solid var(--line);text-decoration:none}.material-grid a:last-child{border:0}.material-grid span{text-transform:uppercase;font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.18em}.material-grid strong{font:400 1.55rem var(--serif)}.carry-section{text-align:center}.carry-section h2,.carry-section .lede{margin-inline:auto}.carry-flow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);margin:4rem 0;border-block:1px solid rgba(238,233,223,.25)}.carry-flow span{padding:1.4rem .5rem;border-right:1px solid rgba(238,233,223,.18);font-size:.72rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em}.carry-flow span:last-child{border:0}.carry-section .actions{justify-content:center}.map-invitation{padding:10rem 0;color:var(--moonlight);background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--ink-deep),rgba(23,24,19,.35)),url('/images/dunhuang/travel-map.png') center/cover}.map-invitation h2{max-width:850px}.map-invitation p{max-width:580px}@media(max-width:800px){.daily-trace .wrap{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:.5rem}.origin-grid,.story-chapters article,.story-chapters article:nth-child(even){grid-template-columns:1fr}.story-chapters article:nth-child(even) .chapter-copy{order:0}.chapter-copy{padding:5rem 1rem}.story-image{min-height:48vw}.path-list a{grid-template-columns:2.4rem 1fr}.path-list em{grid-column:2}.material-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.material-grid a:nth-child(2){border-right:0}.material-grid a{min-height:190px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}.carry-flow{grid-template-columns:1fr}.carry-flow span{border-right:0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(238,233,223,.18)}.map-invitation{padding:6rem 0}}
</style>
<style is:global>
  .home-objects-stories{background:var(--sand-pale)}.home-objects-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);margin:4rem 0 2.2rem;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}.home-objects-grid a{display:flex;min-height:230px;flex-direction:column;padding:1.5rem;border-right:1px solid var(--line);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);color:inherit;text-decoration:none}.home-objects-grid a:last-child{border-right:0}.home-objects-grid span{font:500 .68rem var(--sans);letter-spacing:.13em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--oxidized-jade)}.home-objects-grid strong{margin:1.2rem 0 .65rem;font:400 clamp(1.55rem,2.5vw,2.4rem) var(--serif)}.home-objects-grid p{max-width:21rem;margin:0;color:var(--ink-muted)}.home-objects-grid a:hover strong{text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:.16em}.home-objects-button{background:var(--faded-clay)!important;border-color:var(--faded-clay)!important;color:#fff!important}@media(max-width:700px){.home-objects-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;margin-top:2.5rem}.home-objects-grid a,.home-objects-grid a:last-child{min-height:0;border-right:0}.home-objects-grid .actions{flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start}}
</style>
<style is:global>
  .shop-highlight{background:var(--faded-clay)!important;border-color:var(--faded-clay)!important;color:#fff!important}.shop-highlight:hover{background:var(--sand-light)!important;border-color:var(--sand-light)!important;color:var(--ink-deep)!important}
</style>
